  <prompt>
    Close real-bug-ledger entry **RB-T028-01** by fixing the non-deterministic sort behavior in `AnalysisContextBuilder.BuildContinuationPrompt` (line 115) and `BuildContinuationPromptWithContext` (line 162). The `.OrderByDescending(m => m.Timestamp).Take(_options.MaxChatHistoryMessages).Reverse()` chain drops messages and reorders pairs when multiple messages share the same `Timestamp` tick (observable when concurrent chat messages arrive in a burst — fast typing, LLM streaming).

    Per the ledger §622-643, two equivalent fixes are documented:

    **Option A** (preferred when explicit tiebreaker is acceptable):
    ```csharp
    var indexed = history.Select((m, i) => (msg: m, idx: i));
    var messagesToInclude = indexed
        .OrderByDescending(x => x.msg.Timestamp)
        .ThenByDescending(x => x.idx)
        .Take(_options.MaxChatHistoryMessages)
        .Reverse()
        .Select(x => x.msg)
        .ToArray();
    ```

    **Option B** (cleaner — caller `AnalysisOrchestrationService` already provides chronological order per `Services.Ai.Chat.ChatHistoryService` contract):
    ```csharp
    var messagesToInclude = history
        .TakeLast(_options.MaxChatHistoryMessages)
        .ToArray();
    ```

    Default to **Option B** unless code-review at Step 9.5 surfaces a counter-contract from `ChatHistoryService` source. Apply the fix in BOTH `BuildContinuationPrompt` and `BuildContinuationPromptWithContext` methods (both have the same bug pattern). Per NFR-04 cite `RB-T028-01` + resolution mode `repaired`.
  </prompt>

  <role>Backend AI agent fixing the non-deterministic LLM context-window construction in `Services/Ai/AnalysisContextBuilder`.</role>

  <goal>
    `AnalysisContextBuilder.BuildContinuationPrompt` + `BuildContinuationPromptWithContext` produce deterministic last-N-message windows regardless of timestamp collisions. The `BuildContinuationPrompt_ExceedsMaxHistory_TruncatesToLimit` test flips Skip → Pass. RB-T028-01 transitions to `repaired`.
  </goal>

