  <context>
    <background>
      Per ledger §608-616: `Enumerable.OrderByDescending` is stable, but when many `DateTime.UtcNow` calls execute in a tight loop (e.g., `Enumerable.Range(1,20).Select(...)`), multiple messages get identical `Timestamp` ticks. With ties, `Take(N)` selects an unspecified subset of tied entries; the `Reverse()` operation inverts relative order of remaining ties. Result observed in the failing test: production produces messages 10,12,13,14,15,16,17,18,20,19 instead of 11..20 — **drops Msg-11 and inverts (19, 20)**.

      Both `BuildContinuationPrompt` (line 115) and `BuildContinuationPromptWithContext` (line 162) have the SAME bug pattern at lines 129-133 and 211-215 respectively. The unit test only covers the first method, but the production fix MUST apply to both methods — per the ledger §620.

      Option B (TakeLast) is preferred IF `ChatHistoryService` already provides messages chronologically — verify this contract before defaulting; if violated, use Option A.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="013" status="required">Phase 1 exit triple-run validated</dependency>
      <dependency task="023" status="optional">Conservative dependency — task 023 also touches Services/Ai/Chat module; sequence in Wave 2 to avoid context-builder/resolver edit collision risk</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

