    <step order="4">Apply the chosen option (default B) to BOTH methods. Verify the change preserves chronological output order (caller expects ascending order in the conversation history block).</step>
    <step order="5">Remove `Skip = "..."` + per-test trait override on `BuildContinuationPrompt_ExceedsMaxHistory_TruncatesToLimit` (line 215 of test file).</step>
    <step order="6">Build: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`. Verify 0 errors.</step>
    <step order="7">Run targeted tests: `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~AnalysisContextBuilder"`. Confirm the previously-skipped test passes + other tests in the class remain green.</step>
    <step order="8">Step 9.5 quality gates: `code-review` (verify Option choice is justified vs ChatHistoryService contract) + `adr-check` (ADR-010 / ADR-013).</step>
    <step order="9">Update RB-T028-01 ledger: Status → `repaired`; fix-commit SHA + date; record chosen option in Notes.</step>
    <step order="10">Commit: `fix(ai): make BuildContinuationPrompt deterministic by using TakeLast (RB-T028-01; repaired)` OR `...by adding ThenByDescending tiebreaker (...)`. Update `current-task.md`.</step>
  </steps>

